The force between two point charges is given by Coulomb’s law:  
\[
F = k \frac{|q_1 q_2|}{r^2}
\]  
Here, \(k = 9 \times 10^9 \, \text{N·m}^2/\text{C}^2\), \(q_1 = 10^{-6} \, \text{C}\), \(q_2 = 10^{-4} \, \text{C}\), and \(r = 0.5 \, \text{m}\).  
\[
F = 9 \times 10^9 \times \frac{(10^{-6})(10^{-4})}{(0.5)^2} = 9 \times 10^9 \times \frac{10^{-10}}{0.25} = 9 \times 10^9 \times 4 \times 10^{-10} = 3.6 \, \text{N}
\]  

\boxed{A}
